OL,3,CDrink driver killed partner in crash
OL,4,Cafter drinking 'lager, rum and wine'
OL,6,F"No parent should have to bury a child
OL,7,Fin any circumstances. But the fact
OL,8,Fthat this needless waste of life was
OL,9,Fcaused by a conscious decision made by
OL,10,Fsomeone else makes this even more
OL,11,Funbearable.
OL,13,F"I now struggle to look into the
OL,14,Ffuture and towards the good things
OL,15,Fthat might happen. Now I just wait for
OL,16,Fthe bad things to turn up.
OL,18,FMr Shimwell's father said losing a
OL,19,Fchild at any time, let alone in such
OL,20,Ftragic circumstances changes you
OL,21,Fmentally and physically.
